lity margins are discrete at every k, and re-scoring after removal eliminates ties whenever the removed candidate was in the minority. The proposal's predicted 'structural incapability' at k=5 is not a theorem but an empirically falsifiable claim that the harness can test — and the mechanism's logic is flawed because it conflates 'removing any candidate from a 3-2 split' with 'removing a majority candidate,' when in fact only majority removals cause ties while minority removals cause clean flips.","counterexample":[{"k":5,"base_error":0.20,"critic_precision":0.75,"critic_recall":0.50,"scenario":"3 correct + 2 wrong candidates; critic removes a wrong (minority) candidate; re-scoring yields 3 correct vs 1 wrong = plurality flip (fixed), not a 2-2 tie","harness_advantage_over_SC":"positive net fix count, contradicting 'structural incapability'"}]}